				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="Winter Hammer: Easy Rules for the Soviet-Finnish War" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>Frozen forests, T26 tanks and bitter fighting. The Soviet-Finnish Winter War has it all and now you can delve into it without learning a 500 page rule book.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Winter-Hammer is based on the popular Squad-Hammer game engine and is aimed at beer&amp;amp;pretzels war gaming.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players can pick up the mechanics quickly and with ease, while the rules offer the mechanics you need to set up pick-up battles and fight out a fun war games campaign.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;All you need is some suitable figures in a scale you enjoy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The typical game set up doesn't require more than 10-12 troop stands per player, meaning you can play without having to paint up hundreds of figures.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The only dice needed are simple D6's.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Troop stands can represent from squads to platoons depending on desired scale and based whichever way you prefer.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Games can be played to completion in an hour in many cases.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Compatible with the Squad Hammer generic war game rules and the Russian Civil War version.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
